                <p>
                    <a name="navigatie" id="navigatie"><strong>Navigating the shop</strong></a>
                    <br />
                    You can enter the online shop via the Welcome page by clicking on one of the  categories listed to the left of your screen. Alternatively, you can click on  ‘Catalogue’ at the top of the Welcome page to access all products directly.
        <br />
                    <a href="#top">[Back to top]</a>
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    <a name="zoek" id="zoek"><strong>Product search</strong></a>
                    <br />
                    You can find specific products in the online shop by using the quick search  function on the Welcome page. To use this function, simply enter product you  are looking for or a keyword and click on the ‘search' button below the entry  field. The shop will automatically produce a list of products that match your  query. If you select a product, you will be able to view the details of the  product and add it to your shopping basket.
        <br />
                    You can also make a product  selection based on available budget and required quantity when you have  selected ‘catalogue’ or a category.<br />
                    <a href="#top">[Back to top]</a>
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    <a name="producten" id="producten"><strong>Adding products to your shopping cart</strong></a>
                    <br />
                    To add a product to your shopping cart either select the ‘add to cart’ icon on  the overview page or click on  the  product to open the product detail screen, enter the required quantity and  click on 'Add'. Click on ‘purchase’ on the right side of the screen and on  ‘your cart’ to review the contents of your shopping cart.
        <br />
                    <a href="#top">[Back to top]</a><br />
                    <br />
                    <a name="winkelmandje" id="winkelmandje"><strong>Editing the shopping cart</strong></a>
                    <br />
                    When reviewing the contents of your shopping cart you can always change the  quantity of each ordered product by simply clicking on the ‘quantity’ field,  changing the number of the order and clicking on ‘update’. The content of your  shopping cart will automatically be updated<em>. </em>Please make sure that the quantity of your order does not exceed the  maximum quantity available, as shown in the line below the items.  The order total is displayed at the bottom of  your order list. If you wish to delete a product  from your shopping cart, click the 'delete'  button. If you are satisfied with the contents of your shopping cart, simply  click ‘Next’ to proceed with your order. <a href="#top">
                        <br />
                        [Back to top]</a>
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    <a name="order" id="order"><strong>Ordering the contents of your shopping cart</strong></a>
                    <br />
                    The order in your shopping cart will not be submitted until you have completed  three steps. To process your order correctly, Gemaco requires some  additional information. Please fill in the required information (step 2) and  enter the required delivery address. Your order is now almost ready for Gemaco to process. Please press the ‘next’ button to finalize your order. The  third step enables you to select the required shipping method and payment  method. Please click on ‘confirm’  to  confirm your order. The next screen will state that your order has been  transmitted to Gemaco. If you would like to check the status of your order,  simply click on ‘my account’. By doing so, you will be able to view and follow  the status of your order.<br />
                    <a href="#top">[Back to top]</a>
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    <a name="Stock" id="Stock"><strong>Stock availability</strong></a>
                    <br />
                    All stock quantities are updated constantly, according to the orders entered.  The Customer service desk will resolve any issues arising from simultaneous  order placements.<br />
                    <a href="#top">[Back to top]</a>
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    <a name="status" id="status"><strong>Checking your order status</strong></a>
                    <br />
                    You can check the actual status of each order you have placed. To do so, simply  click on ‘my account’ at the top of your screen. Your contact details as well  as all previously placed orders will appear with the current status.  You can select each of the orders to view  detailed information. After processing the order, Gemaco will assign a  unique reference number, which you will be required to quote when contacting  the Customer Service Desk. The order status screen will show whether and when  the order has been shipped to the delivery address.<br />
                    <a href="#top">[Back to top]</a>
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    <a name="pricingdetails" id="pricingdetails"><strong>Pricing details and INCO terms</strong></a>
                    <br />
                    All orders within the EU will be delivered DDP (INCO  terms 2000, delivered duty paid)  all  orders outside the EU will be delivered DDU (delivered duty unpaid). DDU means  that Gemaco delivers the goods to the requested destination, not cleared  for import. All import related matters such as import duties are the  responsibility of the OPCO.
        <br />
                    All prices are quoted in Euro and are exclusive of  transport costs and VAT.<a href="#top"><br />
                        [Back to top]</a>
